sub_title: Coordinator of International Relations in Hirado, Japan
summary: Josephine Smit is social media coordinator at Japan Museum SieboldHuis. In her position as a social media manager, she practices creative skills such as copywriting and video and photo editing, and also takes on administrative tasks such as writing a content strategy, social media calendar, tracking KPI and SEO while always being enthusiastic and representative. She also works at Hotei Japanese Prints as an employee responsible for exhibition planning, collection documentation and access. In 2022-2023, she also acted as project leader, editor and writer in that position. She obtained her master's degree in Asian Studies (Japan track) at Leiden University in 2020 and was a student at Kobe University in Japan during this study, where she did research at the Graduate School of International Cooperation Studies. She holds a BA Psychology and a BA Japan Studies as well. Her focus during her studies was on Japan's national politics and international relations, but in recent years she has shifted slightly to Japanese art and culture. Josephine aspires to continue her career in Japan, and is open to tips and conversations about this.
